This paper focuses on predicting the popularity of software repositories over time using machine learning techniques. The paper specifically uses LSTM recurrent neural networks and ARIMA time series prediction, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the diffusion of innovation and cross-repository patterns, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.SD (Software Development).
